•The dictionary definition of polymorphism refers to a
principle in biology in which an organism or species can
have many different forms or stages.
•Subclasses of a class can define their own unique
behaviors and yet share some of the same functionality
of the parent class.
•The Java Virtual Machine (JVM) calls the appropriate
method for the object that is referred to in each variable.
•It does not call the method that is defined by the
variable's type.
•This behavior is referred to as virtual method invocation
and demonstrates an aspect of the important
polymorphism features in the Java language.
